records.addlTxt: Defense enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND; expires December 14, 2022.

Defendant Tasheika L Frazier not in court, in custody.  Attorney Thomas John Erickson Aty appeared by video for Tasheika L Frazier.  Attorney Owen M Piotrowski appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 

**JUDGE FEISS AND ALL PARTIES APPEARED VIA ZOOM VIDEO CONFERENCE.** 
Case in Court for Scheduling Conference. Discussion placed on the record. Defense received discovery material and an offer from the State. Defense requested Final PreTrial and Jury Trial dates. Court ordered parties to submit their Motions in Limine, Jury Instructions, and Witness Lists by the Final PreTrial date. Any Motions are due by the Final PreTrial date. If the parties believe a necessary witness for the State or Defense requires independent representation, they are to make arrangements for that representation through the Public Defender's Office two (2) weeks in advance of the Final PreTrial. Court ordered case adjourned for Final PreTrial and (SPEEDY) Jury Trial. Case remains calendared in Branch 46. 

Final PreTrial scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 9:00 am. Hearing will be held via Zoom Video Conference.
(SPEEDY) Jury Trial scheduled for December 12, 2022 at 09:00 am. Trial will be held in Room 113 of the Safety Building.
Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court.

Defendant Tasheika L Frazier in court with attorney Thomas John Erickson; both appear by video.  Defendant Tasheika L Frazier in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Court took judicial notice of 17CF4946 & 17CF5049. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer Leon Woods. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 46.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Thomas John Erickson in court, defendant Tasheika L Frazier not in court, in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is not present. Defense moves to dismiss; motion taken under advisement. Defense to be heard on bail on the next date. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
